**Theorem:** There are infinitely many balanced integers.
**Proof:** Let $k \ge 1$ be an integer. Let $n_k = 2(10^k+1)^2$.
Then $n_k = 2(10^{2k}
 + 2\cdot 10^k + 1) = 2\cdot 10^{2k} + 4\cdot 10^k + 2$.
